      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Hmmm.. my feeling about why it&#39;s not recommended is, because then the static instance in the class is beyond the control of spring. Once injected the static field is <i>the</i> reference for all instances of objects of the corresponding (surrounding) class. But, this behaviour might be exactly what is expected to happen, thus might be seen as a bug or a feature..."
