    "last_edit_date" : 1495540039,
    "creation_date" : 1245663479,
    "answer_id" : 1026298,
    "question_id" : 1018797,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can achieve this using <strong>XML notation</strong> and the <code>MethodInvokingFactoryBean</code>. For an example look <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/28629930/how-can-i-inject-local-variables-of-a-static-method-inside-an-abstract-class-usi/28632156#28632156\">here</a>.</p>\n\n<pre><code>private static StaticBean staticBean;\n\npublic void setStaticBean(StaticBean staticBean) {\n   StaticBean.staticBean = staticBean;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>You should aim to use <strong>spring injection where possible as this is the recommended approach</strong> but this is not always possible as I'm sure you can imagine as not everything can be pulled from the spring container or you maybe dealing with legacy systems.</p>\n\n<p>Note testing can also be more difficult with this approach.</p>\n"
  }, {
